1
00:00:09,700 --> 00:00:11,800
That kid named Mookie
has a high fever.

2
00:00:11,867 --> 00:00:12,933
- What?
- The rain is heavy.

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,033
I'll be right back.

4
00:00:14,100 --> 00:00:14,933
Mookie!
Mookie!

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,333
Did God already answer
my prayer to see you?

6
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:22,800
I know someone who plays
card games like me.

7
00:00:22,867 --> 00:00:24,500
He's not only good at gambling.

8
00:00:24,567 --> 00:00:25,867
He's also a good mechanic.

9
00:00:25,933 --> 00:00:26,833
Is this ours?

10
00:00:26,900 --> 00:00:28,667
You really are so kind, Madame.

11
00:00:28,733 --> 00:00:30,033
Get out. Our employer
will be here any minute!

12
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:31,267
Mom, please.

13
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:32,300
- Flor!
- What?

14
00:00:32,367 --> 00:00:34,033
You can't tell
Ma'am Olive what I did.

15
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:35,667
- Why?
- You left the gate open.

16
00:00:35,733 --> 00:00:36,867
That's why I got in.

17
00:00:36,933 --> 00:00:37,767
What are you doing here?

18
00:00:37,833 --> 00:00:39,300
This is my route
on the way home.

19
00:00:39,367 --> 00:00:41,067
- How about you?
- Can I explain it at home?

20
00:00:41,133 --> 00:00:44,167
You went out and left
Mookie alone in the house?

21
00:00:44,233 --> 00:00:47,067
- I'm sorry, Ma'am.
- I can't lose Mookie.

22
00:00:47,133 --> 00:00:48,967
I won't let that happen!

23
00:00:49,033 --> 00:00:50,000
Let go of me.

24
00:00:50,067 --> 00:00:51,000
I don't want you anymore.

25
00:00:51,067 --> 00:00:53,400
You should be left alone.

26
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:30,033
Mookie!

27
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:31,667
Mookie! Mookie, wait!

28
00:01:31,733 --> 00:01:33,600
Don't leave me!

29
00:01:33,667 --> 00:01:36,167
Mookie!

30
00:01:48,967 --> 00:01:51,833
Mommy, please! I don't want
to stay inside forever.

31
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:53,467
I want to go outside.

32
00:01:53,533 --> 00:01:55,267
Even just in the garden.

33
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:59,067
Please, Mommy.
I will do everything.

34
00:01:59,133 --> 00:02:02,867
Please, Mommy.
Don't deny me of that.

35
00:02:02,933 --> 00:02:05,900
I said no!

36
00:02:08,367 --> 00:02:09,800
You never learn.

37
00:02:09,867 --> 00:02:12,533
You deserve to be punished.
Come here!

38
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:14,900
Come here!

39
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,933
You deserve
that because you're stubborn!

40
00:02:24,033 --> 00:02:25,967
Haven't you been torturing me
for a long time?

41
00:02:26,033 --> 00:02:30,867
So you should be alone.
You should be left behind.

42
00:02:30,933 --> 00:02:32,900
Mookie! Mookie!

43
00:02:32,967 --> 00:02:34,833
Mookie, wait! Don't leave me!

44
00:02:34,900 --> 00:02:37,367
Mookie!

45
00:02:39,067 --> 00:02:40,867
I won't let that happen.

46
00:02:42,333 --> 00:02:46,000
I won't lose Mookie.

47
00:02:46,067 --> 00:02:49,067
My parents left me.

48
00:02:49,167 --> 00:02:51,100
Jeremy also left me.

49
00:02:53,367 --> 00:02:56,867
And Baby Angela
was also taken from me.

50
00:02:56,933 --> 00:02:58,967
I won't let it happen!

51
00:02:59,033 --> 00:03:02,533
I won't lose Mookie!

52
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:03,633
No.

53
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:15,500
She can't leave.

54
00:03:15,567 --> 00:03:18,700
No one can take Mookie from me.

55
00:04:07,300 --> 00:04:09,467
You're thinking about your
employer's daughter again.

56
00:04:10,967 --> 00:04:13,333
Why did you go there?

57
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:16,533
You were lucky
your employer wasn't there.

58
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:17,400
Dan,

59
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:21,800
please don't get mad at me.

60
00:04:21,867 --> 00:04:28,433
But I feel so fond of Mookie.

61
00:04:28,533 --> 00:04:30,500
She seems to be a nice kid.

62
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:33,000
It was my first time seeing her,

63
00:04:33,067 --> 00:04:36,833
but I felt like I had known her
for a long time.

64
00:04:42,633 --> 00:04:43,633
Emma.

65
00:04:47,033 --> 00:04:49,900
I'm just worried that...

66
00:04:49,967 --> 00:04:52,567
you'll have the same experience

67
00:04:52,633 --> 00:04:55,100
with what happened
with Baby Samantha.

68
00:04:55,167 --> 00:04:58,300
Dan, I'm trying not
to get attached to Mookie.

69
00:04:58,367 --> 00:05:03,333
But someone seems to whisper

70
00:05:03,433 --> 00:05:05,333
that I should take care of her.

71
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:10,233
I only want to help her.

72
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:13,900
I want to talk to Ma'am Olive,
but...

73
00:05:13,967 --> 00:05:16,433
I might lose my job.

74
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:17,967
Yes...

75
00:05:18,033 --> 00:05:20,067
that's possible.

76
00:05:20,133 --> 00:05:22,433
You might get fired.

77
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:23,467
Dan...

78
00:05:24,667 --> 00:05:28,167
I've never been
this happy before.

79
00:05:28,233 --> 00:05:30,000
Let me do this.

80
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:37,500
I can't be away from Mookie.

81
00:05:39,367 --> 00:05:48,733
When she didn't
want me to leave...

82
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:52,733
it seemed so painful for me
when she was holding me back.

83
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,733
It's like...

84
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:59,267
someone seemed to tell me
that I shouldn't go,

85
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:03,733
that she needed me,
and I should care for her.

86
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:06,400
Here you go again, Emma.

87
00:06:24,567 --> 00:06:27,067
Did you know
why you had a fever?

88
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:29,800
Why?

89
00:06:30,967 --> 00:06:33,067
Because there is an infection
in your body

90
00:06:33,133 --> 00:06:34,567
that can spread at any time

91
00:06:34,633 --> 00:06:37,300
because of these wounds
on your leg.

92
00:06:37,367 --> 00:06:41,233
But, Mommy,
I don't have a fever anymore.

93
00:06:44,533 --> 00:06:45,933
No, dear.

94
00:06:47,133 --> 00:06:49,400
Your fever will return

95
00:06:49,467 --> 00:06:52,967
if there's still an infection
in your body.

96
00:06:54,767 --> 00:07:01,733
Does that mean I have to take
medicines for infection again?

97
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:04,600
Just like what you always do?

98
00:07:10,167 --> 00:07:13,167
I think your leg
must be amputated

99
00:07:13,233 --> 00:07:17,333
to prevent the infection
from spreading further.

100
00:07:17,433 --> 00:07:18,967
What?

101
00:07:19,033 --> 00:07:20,633
Mommy.

102
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:22,367
Mommy, please, no.

103
00:07:22,433 --> 00:07:25,600
Mommy, please. I don't want
my leg to get amputated.

104
00:07:26,633 --> 00:07:27,700
Well...

105
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,233
What? You'll ask
for another extension?

106
00:07:33,300 --> 00:07:35,500
Come on, Emma!

107
00:07:35,567 --> 00:07:39,200
I'm feeding my family, too!

108
00:07:39,267 --> 00:07:41,100
What's wrong with you?

109
00:07:41,167 --> 00:07:43,900
Miss Tina, I'm sorry.

110
00:07:43,967 --> 00:07:48,400
Danilo's money was used up
for car repairs.

111
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:52,267
But don't worry, I'll pay you
once I get my salary.

112
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:55,267
That's enough.

113
00:07:56,733 --> 00:07:59,100
Show me your hand.
Here's your money.

114
00:07:59,167 --> 00:08:02,200
I think that's enough for now.

115
00:08:02,267 --> 00:08:04,967
And you must stop
yapping, too. Okay?

116
00:08:05,033 --> 00:08:07,067
Fine. This will be good for now.

117
00:08:07,133 --> 00:08:10,033
But you have to pay the rest
of the rent on your payday.

118
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:13,867
- Don't forget that.
- I said that's enough. Go!

119
00:08:13,933 --> 00:08:15,233
Unbelievable.

120
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:16,633
She's not satisfied.

121
00:08:17,767 --> 00:08:18,800
Mom?

122
00:08:18,867 --> 00:08:21,233
Have you won at gambling again?

123
00:08:29,433 --> 00:08:31,700
Hey. What's that?

124
00:08:32,367 --> 00:08:33,800
Madam?

125
00:08:33,867 --> 00:08:36,267
Is this ours?

126
00:08:36,333 --> 00:08:38,200
You really are so kind, Madam.

127
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:40,000
I told you she's kind.

128
00:08:40,067 --> 00:08:42,167
- Thank you!
- Really!

129
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:43,267
Madam!

130
00:08:44,633 --> 00:08:48,767
Didn't I tell you
I already stopped gambling?

131
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:50,733
Your mother
has changed her ways.

132
00:08:54,967 --> 00:08:56,867
Where did you get the money?

133
00:08:59,033 --> 00:09:00,967
I worked for it.

134
00:09:02,033 --> 00:09:05,500
I'm not disabled.
I could get a job.

135
00:09:05,567 --> 00:09:09,233
I'm resourceful
despite being like this.

136
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:10,667
I work part-time.

137
00:09:16,733 --> 00:09:19,400
Didn't I tell you, Mookie,

138
00:09:19,467 --> 00:09:22,267
that even if your legs
are intact,

139
00:09:22,333 --> 00:09:25,300
you still won't be able to walk?

140
00:09:25,367 --> 00:09:29,967
So we really need to do this
to end your suffering.

141
00:09:30,067 --> 00:09:33,367
No, Mommy.
There has to be another way.

142
00:09:33,433 --> 00:09:34,700
Mommy, please.

143
00:09:34,767 --> 00:09:36,500
Don't worry, Mookie.

144
00:09:36,567 --> 00:09:40,933
I know a good orthopedic
surgeon who can do this.

145
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,467
And his clinic is equipped

146
00:09:42,533 --> 00:09:44,333
to handle this kind
of operation.

147
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:46,567
Maybe we can consult
with another doctor, Mommy.

148
00:09:46,633 --> 00:09:49,967
Maybe someone who knows
another way to treat my legs.

149
00:09:50,033 --> 00:09:51,867
Mommy, please.

150
00:09:51,933 --> 00:09:53,767
Mommy, please,

151
00:09:53,833 --> 00:09:59,233
please don't let my legs
get amputated, Mommy.

152
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,767
I'm so sorry, Mookie.

153
00:10:01,867 --> 00:10:04,167
I believe there's no other way.

154
00:10:04,233 --> 00:10:06,767
We need to have
your leg amputated

155
00:10:06,833 --> 00:10:09,733
to prevent the infection
from further spreading

156
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:12,333
because it can kill you.

157
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:16,867
That's why we need to do this
operation as soon as possible.

158
00:10:27,233 --> 00:10:28,467
Hello, Doc Miranda?

159
00:10:29,700 --> 00:10:34,200
Yes, I was the one
who sent you that email.

160
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:36,300
Let's talk about it over dinner.

161
00:10:36,367 --> 00:10:37,100
See you.

162
00:10:41,733 --> 00:10:43,600
Yes, Astrid?

163
00:10:43,667 --> 00:10:45,667
Dr. Miranda?

164
00:10:45,733 --> 00:10:47,867
Isn't he your friend
from medical school

165
00:10:47,933 --> 00:10:50,533
who was expelled
because of malpractice?

166
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,033
Yes, you're correct.

167
00:10:52,100 --> 00:10:55,333
But I believe
it isn't his fault.

168
00:10:56,933 --> 00:11:00,200
But you haven't had any contact
with him for a while, right?

169
00:11:00,267 --> 00:11:02,900
Why did you suddenly reach out?

170
00:11:02,967 --> 00:11:03,867
Olive?

171
00:11:05,067 --> 00:11:07,333
How is Mookie really doing?

172
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,867
Is this about her again?

173
00:11:11,133 --> 00:11:13,400
Astrid, she's fine.

174
00:11:13,467 --> 00:11:16,167
Don't worry about Mookie
too much.

175
00:11:16,233 --> 00:11:17,400
Here.

176
00:11:17,467 --> 00:11:18,967
I have to go.

177
00:11:19,033 --> 00:11:20,500
Mookie's waiting for me.

178
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:40,867
I wonder how Mookie is doing.

179
00:11:50,433 --> 00:11:51,233
Emma?

180
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:57,267
What did you do?

181
00:11:59,300 --> 00:11:59,933
Ma'am?

182
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:04,433
Please let me explain.

183
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:10,433
Do you have any idea
how expensive this dress is?

184
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:15,867
Even a few months of your salary
can't pay for that dress.

185
00:12:15,967 --> 00:12:17,133
Ma'am, I'm sorry.

186
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:22,333
Maybe I didn't notice it,
but this is easy to remove.

187
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,667
Wait.

188
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:35,700
Here you go, Ma'am.
It can be removed.

189
00:12:35,767 --> 00:12:37,267
Good.

190
00:12:37,333 --> 00:12:41,067
If not, I would have fired you.

191
00:12:42,867 --> 00:12:44,767
Do your job well.

192
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:54,933
I hope Mookie's recovery is as
quick as removing this stain.

193
00:12:56,133 --> 00:12:58,100
Emma.

194
00:12:58,167 --> 00:13:02,267
You thought I reported you,
didn't you?

195
00:13:02,333 --> 00:13:03,467
Thank you, Friend.

196
00:13:05,467 --> 00:13:09,200
But that doesn't mean
I have forgotten what you did.

197
00:13:09,267 --> 00:13:13,800
You might get fired
if you do that again.

198
00:13:13,867 --> 00:13:15,600
I won't.

199
00:13:15,667 --> 00:13:17,100
How about Mookie?

200
00:13:17,167 --> 00:13:19,400
How is she? Is she better now?

201
00:13:19,467 --> 00:13:21,333
That's the thing...

202
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:23,567
she has become worse.

203
00:13:23,667 --> 00:13:26,267
I feel bad for her.
She keeps on crying.

204
00:13:26,333 --> 00:13:30,733
Her mom said her leg
needed to get amputated.

205
00:13:33,567 --> 00:13:35,133
Mommy, please!
I'll do everything.

206
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:38,133
Promise! I'll do everything
you want me to do.

207
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:40,500
I won't go out. I'll behave.

208
00:13:40,567 --> 00:13:43,433
Mommy, please.
Just don't amputate my leg!

209
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:44,700
Mommy, please.

210
00:13:44,767 --> 00:13:46,033
Flor!

211
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:47,100
Ma'am Olive is calling me.

212
00:13:47,167 --> 00:13:48,233
Stay here, okay?

213
00:14:00,033 --> 00:14:01,133
Ma'am?

214
00:14:02,933 --> 00:14:05,000
- Mookie, dear.
- Mommy.

215
00:14:05,067 --> 00:14:08,100
- I heard that before.
- I don't want to.

216
00:14:08,167 --> 00:14:12,800
But you know, I'm actually
doing this for your own good.

217
00:14:12,867 --> 00:14:16,367
Because I don't want anything
bad to happen to you.

218
00:14:16,433 --> 00:14:21,700
And I don't want to lose you.

219
00:14:21,767 --> 00:14:25,867
Mommy, please.
I don't want it. Mommy!

220
00:14:25,933 --> 00:14:28,167
Mommy, please!

221
00:14:28,267 --> 00:14:30,600
Hello, Doc Miranda?

222
00:14:30,667 --> 00:14:32,300
Yes, we're on our way there.

223
00:14:32,367 --> 00:14:36,700
Flor, please get Mookie's stuff
that we're going to bring.

224
00:14:36,767 --> 00:14:38,667
- Yes, Doc.
- Mookie.

225
00:14:38,733 --> 00:14:39,833
Mookie.

226
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:41,300
I know.

227
00:14:41,367 --> 00:14:42,867
I'm sorry.

228
00:14:42,933 --> 00:14:46,333
It's best if we listen, okay?

229
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:49,167
Okay? Be strong.

230
00:14:49,233 --> 00:14:51,667
I can't do anything. Sorry.

231
00:14:51,733 --> 00:14:54,533
I'm sorry.

232
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:58,500
I'll just get your clothes.
I'll get them. Wait.

233
00:15:10,667 --> 00:15:12,000
Mookie!

234
00:15:12,067 --> 00:15:14,367
Mookie!

235
00:15:14,433 --> 00:15:15,533
Mommy Emma!

236
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:19,633
Mommy Emma!

237
00:15:19,700 --> 00:15:20,600
Stay there.

238
00:15:20,667 --> 00:15:22,400
Don't come near here.

239
00:15:22,467 --> 00:15:24,733
Your mommy might see us.

240
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:28,867
Please help me convince my mom
not to amputate my leg.

241
00:15:28,933 --> 00:15:31,433
Please, I'm begging you!

242
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:33,400
Please!

243
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:39,933
Don't worry, Doc.
No one will know about our plan.

244
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:43,333
Oh, by the way, have you
checked your bank account?

245
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:45,433
I'm sure you'd be delighted
to see the amount

246
00:15:45,500 --> 00:15:47,133
I transferred to you.

247
00:16:07,733 --> 00:16:09,933
Please.

248
00:16:10,033 --> 00:16:15,333
Help me convince mommy
not to amputate my leg, please.

249
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:16,333
Mookie.

250
00:16:16,400 --> 00:16:18,500
Mookie, I want to help you.

251
00:16:18,567 --> 00:16:20,967
But I can't do anything.

252
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:25,433
I can't meddle
with your mom's decisions.

253
00:16:25,500 --> 00:16:27,800
And she's a doctor.

254
00:16:27,867 --> 00:16:31,900
But I don't understand why
she wants to amputate your leg.

255
00:16:31,967 --> 00:16:33,867
I don't get that.

256
00:16:33,933 --> 00:16:36,600
No. I don't want it, please!

257
00:16:36,667 --> 00:16:39,500
I don't want to!

258
00:16:39,567 --> 00:16:40,933
Mookie?

259
00:16:42,767 --> 00:16:46,100
Who are you talking to?

260
00:16:46,167 --> 00:16:48,433
Who are you talking to?

261
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:54,167
I don't want to do it, Mommy!

262
00:16:54,233 --> 00:16:55,567
I don't want it!

263
00:16:55,633 --> 00:16:57,900
Who are you talking to?

264
00:16:57,967 --> 00:16:59,100
I don't want it!

265
00:16:59,167 --> 00:17:01,533
I don't want my leg
to get amputated!

266
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:04,033
Stop crying.

267
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:07,933
- We need to go.
- Mommy!

268
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,000
- Mommy!
- Hello?

269
00:17:10,067 --> 00:17:14,567
- Mommy!
- Yes, Mrs. Ricamonte?

270
00:17:14,633 --> 00:17:16,533
Here are your things.

271
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:20,033
When is this?

272
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:27,067
Hey, Emma!

273
00:17:27,133 --> 00:17:30,167
What are you doing here?
Our employer might see you!

274
00:17:30,233 --> 00:17:32,033
I have urgent matters
to attend to.

275
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:35,033
But maybe I will just send...

276
00:17:35,100 --> 00:17:36,367
Mookie?

277
00:17:41,267 --> 00:17:42,700
I'm sorry.

278
00:17:42,767 --> 00:17:46,600
I just feel bad for Mookie.

279
00:17:46,667 --> 00:17:49,167
Flor, it will affect her
significantly

280
00:17:49,267 --> 00:17:51,567
if her leg gets amputated.

281
00:17:51,633 --> 00:17:53,167
What about her dreams?

282
00:17:53,233 --> 00:17:54,933
Her future?

283
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:57,900
She might lose her will to live.

284
00:17:57,967 --> 00:17:59,767
Mommy!

285
00:17:59,833 --> 00:18:02,033
Mommy!

286
00:18:02,100 --> 00:18:04,367
Stop crying, Mookie!

287
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:08,667
What are you doing? Don't.

288
00:18:08,733 --> 00:18:11,200
We'll get in trouble.

289
00:18:11,267 --> 00:18:13,833
She's asking for help.
Don't you feel bad for her?

290
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:14,833
I do.

291
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:17,633
Who won't?

292
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:19,700
But what can we do?

293
00:18:19,767 --> 00:18:21,433
Do we know anything?

294
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:25,467
Ma'am Olive is Mookie's mother,
not us.

295
00:18:25,567 --> 00:18:28,933
She knows what's best
for Mookie.

296
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:31,333
Let's stay here. Let's just
listen to what she says.

297
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:34,667
Flor!

298
00:18:34,733 --> 00:18:35,967
Flor!

299
00:18:36,033 --> 00:18:38,167
- Please help me.
- Flor, help me out here!

300
00:18:38,233 --> 00:18:39,600
- I don't want to do this.
- Yes, Ma'am.

301
00:18:39,667 --> 00:18:42,067
- No, I don't want this.
- Let's go.

302
00:18:42,133 --> 00:18:45,467
- Up, come on.
- No, no, Mommy, please.

303
00:18:45,533 --> 00:18:49,267
- No, no, Mommy.
- Stop it.

304
00:18:49,333 --> 00:18:52,567
- Please lift Mookie up.
- Okay, Ma'am.

305
00:18:52,633 --> 00:18:53,833
Sorry.

306
00:19:04,967 --> 00:19:07,200
Mommy, please,
I'll do everything.

307
00:19:07,267 --> 00:19:08,700
I'll do everything, Mommy,

308
00:19:08,767 --> 00:19:12,167
just don't amputate my leg,
Mommy.

309
00:19:12,233 --> 00:19:15,233
I don't want it, Mommy! Please.

310
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:18,167
Mommy! I can't bear it, Mommy.

311
00:19:18,233 --> 00:19:21,033
My life will never be
normal again.

312
00:19:21,100 --> 00:19:22,700
Mommy, please. Please, Mommy.

313
00:19:22,767 --> 00:19:24,733
I really don't want
to lose my leg.

314
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,233
Mommy, please.

315
00:19:26,300 --> 00:19:28,933
But you will live
without suffering.

316
00:19:29,033 --> 00:19:30,267
You'll be in so much pain

317
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:33,167
if we don't have
your leg amputated.

318
00:19:33,233 --> 00:19:34,967
And it's even more painful
for a mother

319
00:19:35,033 --> 00:19:37,900
to see her child suffering.

320
00:19:37,967 --> 00:19:38,933
And worse...

321
00:19:40,700 --> 00:19:45,067
you might die
if we don't do this.

322
00:19:47,633 --> 00:19:49,200
Where's Angela?

323
00:19:49,267 --> 00:19:50,267
I'm so sorry.

324
00:19:50,333 --> 00:19:53,900
No! No!

325
00:19:53,967 --> 00:19:55,833
No!

326
00:19:55,900 --> 00:19:57,800
I won't let that happen!

327
00:19:57,867 --> 00:19:59,267
I'll go insane!

328
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:02,800
I can't bear it if you die!

329
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:05,000
So I will have your legs
amputated

330
00:20:05,067 --> 00:20:07,400
so that you will stay
with me forever!

331
00:20:07,467 --> 00:20:10,267
Please, Mommy.
I really don't want to!

332
00:20:10,333 --> 00:20:12,700
Please, Mommy!

333
00:20:14,667 --> 00:20:16,633
Flor, what do we do?

334
00:20:16,700 --> 00:20:18,500
I don't know either.

335
00:20:18,567 --> 00:20:20,133
I'm also nervous.

336
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:22,600
Let's just pray.

337
00:20:22,667 --> 00:20:25,267
I hope it won't push through.

338
00:20:25,333 --> 00:20:28,433
Poor Mookie.

339
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:29,567
Flor?

340
00:20:29,633 --> 00:20:31,200
- Flor, where are you?
- Ma'am Astrid!

341
00:20:31,267 --> 00:20:33,367
We're here, Ma'am!

342
00:20:33,433 --> 00:20:35,467
I'm glad Ma'am Astrid is here.

343
00:20:36,333 --> 00:20:37,800
Ma'am.

344
00:20:37,867 --> 00:20:39,967
Flor, Emma,
where are the people here?

345
00:20:40,033 --> 00:20:42,167
- Ma'am Astrid.
- Where are Mookie and Olive?

346
00:20:42,233 --> 00:20:45,600
Ma'am, Ma'am. Ma'am Olive
brought Mookie to the hospital.

347
00:20:45,667 --> 00:20:47,800
She said Mookie's leg
should be amputated.

348
00:20:47,867 --> 00:20:49,000
What?

349
00:20:51,667 --> 00:20:53,700
Ma'am, maybe you can help her.

350
00:20:57,133 --> 00:20:59,533
Hello, Doc Miranda?

351
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:01,933
Yes, I was the one
who sent you that email.

352
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,600
Let's talk about it over dinner.

353
00:21:04,667 --> 00:21:06,633
Isn't he your friend
from medical school

354
00:21:06,700 --> 00:21:09,633
who got expelled
because of malpractice?

355
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:15,800
I'm sorry.

356
00:21:19,533 --> 00:21:22,233
I'm sorry, all circuits
are busy now.

357
00:21:26,733 --> 00:21:29,200
- I'll go ahead, wait bye.
- Okay, Ma'am. Bye.

358
00:21:29,267 --> 00:21:30,467
Be safe.

359
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:36,300
I hope Ma'am Astrid
catches up to them.

360
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,867
Mommy, please!

361
00:21:42,933 --> 00:21:45,700
Mommy, please.
I don't want this, Mommy.

362
00:21:45,767 --> 00:21:48,033
Mommy, please.
Please. Mommy, please.

363
00:21:48,100 --> 00:21:49,800
- It's going to be okay.
- Please, Mommy.

364
00:21:49,867 --> 00:21:52,700
Please. Let's go home, Mommy.

365
00:21:52,767 --> 00:21:55,333
Mommy, please!

366
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:58,467
Please, Mommy! I don't want to!

367
00:21:58,533 --> 00:22:01,267
- Please be gentle with her.
- I don't want this, please!

368
00:22:01,333 --> 00:22:03,000
- Please, Mommy!
- Don't worry.

369
00:22:03,067 --> 00:22:05,000
Your daughter is in good hands.

370
00:22:05,067 --> 00:22:08,833
- Mommy! Please let's go home!
- Mookie.

371
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:12,267
I don't want this!
No, Mommy, please!

372
00:22:12,333 --> 00:22:13,700
Doc, stop.

373
00:22:13,767 --> 00:22:14,967
- Stop.
- Mommy, please.

374
00:22:15,067 --> 00:22:18,667
- Let's stop first.
- Please, Mommy, please.

375
00:22:18,733 --> 00:22:21,733
- Please, please, Mommy.
- It's okay. Mommy's here.

376
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:26,100
Mommy, please.

377
00:22:26,167 --> 00:22:28,900
- Mommy, please.
- It's okay.

378
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:33,133
Just count to 10, okay?

379
00:23:20,633 --> 00:23:22,533
Doc, Doc.

380
00:23:22,633 --> 00:23:23,900
I'm so sorry.

381
00:23:25,567 --> 00:23:27,600
Let's not do it.

382
00:23:27,667 --> 00:23:29,233
What?

383
00:23:29,300 --> 00:23:31,667
- But, Olive...
- I know, I know.

384
00:23:34,667 --> 00:23:36,100
I can't do this
to my daughter.

385
00:23:37,700 --> 00:23:39,833
We have an agreement.

386
00:23:39,900 --> 00:23:42,833
- I canceled a surgery for this.
- I know, Doc.

387
00:23:42,900 --> 00:23:45,200
I'm so sorry. I'm sorry.

388
00:23:45,267 --> 00:23:47,900
And don't worry.
I will still pay you in full.

389
00:23:47,967 --> 00:23:49,700
Let's just not do this.

390
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:52,600
Okay. Nurse.

391
00:23:56,300 --> 00:23:57,633
What?

392
00:23:57,700 --> 00:23:59,500
Why?

393
00:23:59,567 --> 00:24:01,600
- What's going on?
- The police are here.

394
00:24:01,667 --> 00:24:05,033
- What?
- Someone reported me again.

395
00:24:05,100 --> 00:24:09,500
Olive, you better leave.
They can't see a patient here.

396
00:24:09,567 --> 00:24:11,300
What?

397
00:24:11,367 --> 00:24:12,767
Mookie!

398
00:24:14,100 --> 00:24:15,667
Mookie.

399
00:24:19,933 --> 00:24:22,767
I can't bear to see her
without her legs.

400
00:24:22,833 --> 00:24:26,333
You seem to be getting
too attached to Mookie.

401
00:24:26,400 --> 00:24:28,500
We can adopt a child
if you like.

402
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:32,067
So you won't have
to use your time

403
00:24:32,133 --> 00:24:34,367
for a kid not related to you.

404
00:24:34,433 --> 00:24:36,567
See, Mommy? I can now stand.

405
00:24:36,633 --> 00:24:38,300
Maybe I can walk soon.

406
00:24:38,367 --> 00:24:41,567
I will never let you
walk again, Mookie.

407
00:24:41,633 --> 00:24:43,600
You are mine forever.

408
00:24:47,067 --> 00:24:47,900
Damn it!

409
00:24:47,967 --> 00:24:50,133
Do you want
to practice walking?

410
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:54,067
I really want to because
I don't want to lose my leg.

411
00:24:58,400 --> 00:25:01,767
- Give me your cell phone!
- Let go of me! Hey!
